To calculate the Gross Profit Margin, we use the following formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{\text{Gross Profit}}{\text{Total Revenue}} \right) \times 100 \]

From the given problem:
- Gross Profit = 194,172.30
- Total Revenue = 547,392.30

Now, plug these values into the formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{194,172.30}{547,392.30} \right) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 0.3547 \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 35.47\% \]

So, the solution is:

```json
{"solution": {'Gross Profit Margin': '35.47%'} }
```
